title: It's official: BN wins Tanjong Datu by-election with increased majority
text:
LUNDU: Barisan Nasional has won the Tanjong Datu by-election with a landslide majority of 6,443 votes.

Puan Sri Jamilah Anu, 61, got 6,573 votes over Rapelson Richard Hamit of PBDS Baru and STAR's Johnny Bob Aput, who managed only 130 and 108 votes respectively. Both candidates lost their deposit.

The Tanjong Datu seat fell vacant following the death of Sarawak chief minister Tan Sri Adenan Satem on Jan 11.

Jamilah, Adenanâ€™s widow, recorded an increased majority of about 12% compared with Adenan's 5,892 vote-majority in the May 2016 state polls.

At early voting on Feb 12, Barisan obtained 157 votes, while STAR and PBDS Baru received one vote each. Barisan also obtained 40 postal votes, while the two other parties received none.

Returning officer Hamsein Atar officially declared Jamilah the winner at 8pm Saturday.

Total turnout for the by-election was 69%, with 70 spoilt votes.
